english_title: Living Life to the Fullest (Ain't No Need to Mask)
content_vision: We met at the bar. I said the most stupid line in the world to impress you. You laughed and kissed me.
structure_suggestion_description: We met at the bar. I said the most stupid line in the world to impress you. You laughed and kissed me.
text:
Intro:
you need to get a life, boy, reachin' too far,
like a perfect match made in the stars,

Verse 1:
no need for the lotto, i ball hard anyway
and my guidance, it knows to agree with my way.
we just them niggas you ain't messing with,
they better motherfuckin listen or they'll feel the wrath of our hit.
you missing out on my greatness, i'm killing the game,
while these niggas still talking shit about me in the barber's chain.
everything fell apart, and it all went south,
but she held me tight, put a rock on me real loud.

Chorus 1:
riding through the city, on a mission tonight,
ain't nobody gonna stop us, 'cause we're feeling alright.
you know what time it is, ain't no need to ask,
we're living life to the fullest, ain't no need to mask.

Verse 2:
all my clothes migrated, ain't no worries, i'm still fly
my virtue slipped into my shoe, ain't gotta try
just listen to the rhythm of this king kong song, let it take you high.
gotta let my heart ride different beats,
keep way more not tryna stress and compete,
30 all up in my nina, that's how we defeat.
cruising on easy street, it's like a 1- 2- 3,
we'll get there together, roof down, no more worries.

Chorus 2:
she said not you, but i'm still gon shine,
why you wanna hurt yourself, wasting time?
i'm shinning like the summer, making moves that's divine.
and it never seemed strange, i was always on the grind,

Verse 3:
i used to know who i was, but everything's changed,
she worked all night, till the dawn, but now i feel estranged.
life flies by, it feels like i was just a lil' kid,
bitch go brrah, fuck what you heard, i'm never gonna quit.
my life's a comedy, so funny it's sad,
but you need the time to see through the act i've had.
city life's a treadmill, it's got you running,
and you're not the same since it all begun- nning.

Chorus 3:
i'm tryna be a better man, it's a tough climb,
you know i would feel it, love never a waste of time,
seems like everybody knows me now, but they don't know the grind.
she ride for me, she hold me down,

Bridge:
meet me at the function, but i can't make up my mind,
it's a battle between my heart and my pride.
you got too much time on your hands, not a care,
but i can't afford to lose them, gotta move and share.

Outro:
life flies by, it feels like i was just a lil' kid,
bitch go brrah, fuck what you heard, i'm never gonna quit.

Instrumental:
no need for the lotto, i ball hard anyway
and my guidance, it knows to agree with my way.

active_struct.name: The Unconventional Form
attrs: has a simpler structure with a focus on repeating verses and choruses
allows for instrumental breaks and added dynamic in the verses
suitable for a shorter song or for a more repetitive melody

struct_suggs.name: The Climactic Connection
attrs: dynamic and engaging
includes a strong intro and outro
has a clear progression from verse to chorus and back
suitable for a medium-length song

struct_suggs.name: The Narrative Journey
attrs: allows for story arc development with multiple verses and choruses
a bridge and prechorus add variety and build up to the final chorus
has a distinct intro and outro
suitable for a longer song

struct_suggs.name: The Multilayered Melody
attrs: has multiple prechoruses and choruses, allowing for a buildup towards the climax
includes a bridge for a change in pace and tone
has a clear structure with consistent parts
suitable for a medium-length song

struct_suggs.name: The Unconventional Form
attrs: has a simpler structure with a focus on repeating verses and choruses
allows for instrumental breaks and added dynamic in the verses
suitable for a shorter song or for a more repetitive melody

struct_suggs.name: The Surprising Switch-Up
attrs: includes multiple prechoruses and choruses, creating a gradual buildup towards the climax
has a bridge and instrumental breaks for added variety
allows for a longer song with a strong story arc

struct_suggs.name: The Experimental Flow
attrs: has a unique structure with a prechorus in the first verse and no prechorus in the second
suitable for a shorter song with a simple but dynamic structure
the inclusion of a bridge adds variety and interest to the song

struct_suggs.name: The Dynamic Build-Up
attrs: allows for a buildup towards the climax as the prechorus is repeated multiple times
has a shorter chorus and a longer verse, creating an interesting balance within the song
the inclusion of instrumental breaks adds variation and dynamic to the structure

struct_suggs.name: The Dramatic Breakdown
attrs: has a unique structure with a prechorus in the first verse and a bridge before the second chorus
the repeated chorus at the end creates a sense of closure in the song
suitable for a medium-length song with added intrigue and variety

struct_suggs.name: The Unexpected Interlude
attrs: has a clear progression from verse to chorus and back, with an added prechorus in between
allows for story development with different perspectives in the verses
suitable for a medium-length song that tells a cohesive story

struct_suggs.name: The Progressive Patterns
attrs: has a unique structure with an intro followed by a verse, creating a compelling start to the song
includes multiple prechoruses and verses, creating a gradual buildup towards the climax
the addition of a bridge and instrumental breaks add dynamic and interest to the structure
suitable for a longer song with a clear story arc.

Chorus 1:

Verse 2:

Chorus 2:

i don't need no bling, i got enough up in my toe,
keepin' me grounded, stayin' true to the code.

Verse 3:
if you ain't got no skills, you can't roll with the crew,
this section only for the baddest, take notes from sam's rhymes too.
she my bitch, gotta keep her in line,
she fuckin' up my flow, gotta keep her in check,
but when we get there together, ain't nothin' gonna make us wreck.
bottles all over, we're living in excess,
but if i say i love you in the candlelight, will you still be impressed?
i see 'em fallin from up the sky,

Chorus 3:

but they still wanna know what's up,
listen to me cause i'll tell you the facts and the buts.

Bridge:
i just wanna put my dick all in her, give her a good time,
baby you would make me oh so fine, in this life and in mine.

but you still lie to my face, can't deal with it.

Outro:
nigga what you sayin', you talkin' 'bout slim shady?

Instrumental:
everybody gotta deal, but what's it all for?
they made you seem like you needed more.

Verse 1:
i'm about to explode, can't contain this rage,
always trying to start another war, trying to set the stage.
shoot your sprinter up, leave your past behind,
you ever wanted something, now's the time to climb.
it ain't no use turnin' on your light,
this world is so wrong, gotta put up a fight.
i sip on that pine while she rides my magic stick,
all the stress, she smokes it away, it's like a magic trick.

Chorus 1:
feel my words, they cut like a blade,
we just them niggas you ain't fuckin' with, we never fade.
i see all these abusers, they think they're so tough,
but i'm done with it all, bout to elope, just enough,

Verse 2:
always reachin' for the stars and higher,
seems like everyone knows who i am now, like a fire.
need that bread to survive, that's no surprise,
the world's so crazy, but still we try,
how we supposed to make it, but still we strive.
i put on my fake smile and dance the night away,
riding with the windows down, living for today.
but days turn to weeks and i just can't escape, this cycle of life is like an endless parade.

Chorus 2:
you better fuck me all night, i'm begging, don't stop,
you know what the fuck i want, baby, give it all you got,
won't you take me close to you, let me show you my love
that's all i ever wanted, all i ever dreamed of.

Verse 3:
why they always tryna copy my style and my groove,
but i ain't lettin' that bring me down, i just keep doin' what i do,
even when we goin' down, down, down, we still makin' moves.
no need to fight, i got a blank check in my hand,
and your bleeding heart, i'll make it understand.
these shoes make me a fashionista, they scream luxury,
they spoiled but i worked hard to afford 'em, you gotta see.
so why do i exist, what's my purpose, where's my mission?

Chorus 3:
everybody knows it's your time to shine,
you play the lead clown but you still getting dimes.
you in my way, i'm trying to find where we went wrong,
she love the way we flexin', puttin' her in a song.

Bridge:
you know that i'm bout to wake up by your side,
we can finance and still leave room for fries,
big macs, supersized, living the life.
veni, vidi, vici, that's how it goes,

Outro:
they say money rules everything, it makes the world go round,
but everybody suffers, that's all i really need to sound.

Intro:
everyone's after the money, it's the root of all evil and danger,
but they'll never catch us, cause we're slicker than a snitch to a stranger.

you actin' like a fool, but damn you look so fine
don't need no words, you know you caught my eye tonight.

all night long, they keep reappearin',
you leave me no choice but to keep goin' down, down, down,
no stoppin' now, we keep grindin' til we wearin' the crown.
these rappers can't keep their heads up, getting sewed,

Chorus 1:

but she loves how we shine, out here flexin' so stark,

Instrumental:

Chorus:

gonna keep pushing when the doors close, no surprise.

Verse 2:
